====== 1 ======
Mahjong ( Traditional Chinese : &#x9EBB ; &#x5C07 ; ; Simplified Chinese : &#x9EBB ; &#x5C06 ; ; Hanyu Pinyin : Májiàng ; Cantonese : Màhjeung ; or Chinese : &#x9EBB ; &#x5C06 ; ; Hanyu Pinyin : Májiàng ; Cantonese : Màhjeuk ; other common English spellings include mahjongg , majiang , and hyphenated forms such as mah-jong or mah-jongg ) is a game for four players that originated in China . 
It involves skill , strategy , and calculation , as well as luck . 
Depending on the variation which is played , luck can be anything from a minor to a dominant factor in success . 
In Asia , mahjong is as popular as gambling or computer games . 
====== 7 ======
The object of the game is to build complete suits - or melds ( usually of threes ) - from either 13 or 16 tiles . 
The first person to achieve this goal wins the game . 
The winning tile completes the player 's set of either 14 or 17 tiles . 
One of the myths of the origin of Mahjong suggests that Confucius , the great Chinese philosopher , had developed the game in about 500 BC . 
====== 6 ======
This assertion is likely to be apocryphal . 
According to this myth , the appearance of the game in the various Chinese states coincided with Confucius ' travels at the time he was teaching his new doctrines . 
The three dragon ( Cardinal ) tiles also agree with the three Cardinal virtues bequeathed by Confucius . 
