The term dragon tile is a western convention introduced by Joseph Park Babcock in his 1920 book introducing Mahjong to America . 
Originally , these tiles are said to have something to do with the Chinese Imperial Examination . 
The red tile ( " &#x4E2D ; " &#x699C ; , zh&#x14D ; ngb&#x1CE ; ng ) means you pass the examination and thus will be appointed a government official . 
====== 5 ======
The green tile ( " &#x767C ; " &#x8CA1 ; , f&#x101 ; cái ) means , consequently you will become financially well off . 
The white tile ( a clean board ) means that because a person is doing well they should act like a good , incorrupt official . 
